Package: callbackConnection
Type: Package
Title: A connection target for R allowing arbitrary R code execution on stdout and stderr messages
Version: 0.1.0
Author: c(
    person(
        given = "Doug", family = "Kelkhoff",
        email = "kelkhoff.douglas@gene.com", role = c("aut", "cre")))
Maintainer: Doug Kelkhoff <kelkhoff.douglas@gene.com>
Description: Provides an interface to constructing a connection target and 
    linking a function to execute with each message passed to the connection. 
    This enables special handling of how a the connection output is written or 
    broken up, logged to a database, handled within a separate language or any 
    other arbitrary processing of the connection output.
License: Artistic-2.0
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.1.1
Imports:
    utils
